<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2999] Addition of .gitattributes text auto in THRIFT-2724 causes modified files on checkout</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2999</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The addition of .gitattributes text auto in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2724&quot; title=&quot;Coding standards page&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-2724&quot;&gt;THRIFT-2724&lt;/a&gt; causes modified files to appear on initial Apache Thrift repo checkout (e.g. git clone) on some linux systems. Most of these files are CR/LF windows files. This patch checks in the files with LF endings to avoid phantom checkouts and to reenable correct diffs and status, also fixes a few whitespace errors. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;linux&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
